					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><figure class="mw-halign-right" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Badugi_nuts.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Badugi_nuts.jpg/200px-Badugi_nuts.jpg" decoding="async" width="200" height="251" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Badugi_nuts.jpg/300px-Badugi_nuts.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Badugi_nuts.jpg/400px-Badugi_nuts.jpg 2x" data-file-width="873" data-file-height="1095" /></a><figcaption>A hand of playing cards</figcaption></figure>
<p><a href="https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Playing_card" class="extiw" title="w:Playing card">Playing cards</a> can be used to play a lot of games (like <a href="https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poker" class="extiw" title="w:Poker">Poker</a>, <a href="https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spoons" class="extiw" title="w:Spoons">Spoons</a>, 21 or Black Jack, and so on). This book is about how to play these games.
</p>
